                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/6019: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-19T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 19, 1937—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 19—8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1010. With regard to Spain, Delbos remarked to me this evening that he did not
                    believe there was any chance of the British proposal being accepted. It would,
                    however, serve to delay a crisis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
